explanation: Dynamic programming approach to track the minimum ASCII sum of deleted characters. The DP table `dp[i][j]` represents the minimum ASCII sum to make `s1[0..i-1]` and `s2[0..j-1]` equal. If characters match, no deletion cost is added; otherwise, the minimum cost between deleting from `s1` or `s2` is chosen.

